kpi_info.title: HS_DSCH_CREDIT_RDCT_DUE_DLY (M5000C176)
kpi_info.use: Number of 10ms congestion control iterations in which the Iub throughput of connections originating from CRNC was controlled by Congestion Control based on trigger "the measured average delay build-up was over minimum delay threshold but below middle delay threshold". Conservatively, the value contains also the iterations directly following the initial total credit reduction until total credits granted to RNC recover and exceed the measured Iub throughput at the time of previous congestion detection by half or until a new throughput reduction is applied with different cause. All cells controlled by same congestion control entity display identical values in this counter because the Iub resource shared by congestion control is common for them. Note that only one of the M5000C176...C178 or M5000C453 may increment by 1 in 10ms iteration. UPDATED: Congestion Control entity remembers the congestion type of previous total credit reduction. In each 10ms iteration, in case the type was "delay build-up" and "total credits" granted to RNC have not yet recovered from the reduction (with conservative safety margin to account for longer RTTs) it increments M5000C176 by one. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

Note that only one of the M5000C176...C179 may increment by 1 in 10ms iteration. UPDATED: Congestion Control entity remembers the congestion type of previous total credit reduction. kpi_info.title: SUM_HSUPA_USERS_2MS_TTI (M5000C324)
kpi_info.use: The sum of sampled values for the number of configured HSUPA users with 2ms TTI. This counter, divided by the denominator M5000C326, provides the average user amount during the measurement interval. UPDATED:The number of users is sampled with 100 ms period and summed to this counter.

kpi_info.title: SUM_HSUPA_USERS_10MS_TTI (M5000C325)
kpi_info.use: The sum of sampled values for the number of configured HSUPA users with 10ms TTI. This counter, divided by the denominator M5000C326, provides the average user amount during the measurement interval. UPDATED:The number of users is sampled with 100 ms period and summed to this counter.

kpi_info.title: DENOM_HSUPA_USERS (M5000C326)
kpi_info.use: The number of samples taken for counters M5000C324 sum of HSUPA users with 2 ms TTI and M5000C325 sum of HSUPA users with 10 ms TTI, needed for average calculation. UPDATED:The counter is updated by value 1 when the number of users is sampled periodically.

kpi_info.title: DENOM_CPC_USERS (M5000C327)
kpi_info.use: This is a general denominator for cell specific user calculations. The counter is needed for the user amount average calculation. UPDATED:The counter is updated by value 1 when the number of users is sampled periodically.

kpi_info.title: ACTIVE_DC_HSDPA_USERS_2C_SUM (M5000C328)
kpi_info.use: The sum of sampled values for the number of active DC-HSDPA users. Active DC users use both carriers for transmission. UPDATED: The sampled number of users is added to this counter. The number of DC users is counted at the last TTI of each 100 ms period (50th TTI) and the counter is increased with this value. Only DC users that use both carriers for transmission in that last TTI of the interval are counted. The counter is updated for both (primary and secondary) cells.

kpi_info.title: ACTIVE_DC_HSDPA_USERS_1C_SUM (M5000C329)
kpi_info.use: The sum of sampled values for the number of active DC-HSDPA users. Active DC users use only one carrier for transmission. UPDATED: The sampled number of users is added to this counter. The number of DC users is counted at the last TTI of each 100 ms period (50th TTI) and the counter is increased with this value. Only DC users that use only one carrier for transmission in that last TTI of the interval are counted. The counter is updated only for the cell in which user data is transmitted.

kpi_info.title: CAPABLE_DC_HSDPA_USERS_SUM (M5000C330)
kpi_info.use: The sum of sampled values for the number of capable DC-HSDPA users. UPDATED: The sampled number of users is added to this counter when sampled value is for capable DC-HSDPA user. The number of DC HSDPA capable users is counted at the last TTI of each 100 ms period (50th TTI) and the counter is increased with this value. For this counter, only those DC users are considered that have data in at least one of their priority queues.

kpi_info.title: TTI_DC_HSDPA_USER_PRIMARY_1C (M5000C331)
kpi_info.use: Number of TTIs for scheduled DC-HSDPA users only, from primary carrier when one carrier is used. UPDATED: The counter is updated by 1 if TTI was scheduled from primary carrier when only one carrier was used.

kpi_info.use: Duration of UE in HSFACH RX (Reception) state. Granularity of the counter is 10 ms. UPDATED: This counter is updated when the UE state is changing to the DRX state.

kpi_info.use: Duration of UE in HSFACH DRX (Discontinuous Reception) state. Granularity of the counter is 10 ms. UPDATED: This counter is updated when the UE state is changing to the RX state.

kpi_info.title: EFACH_UE_SUM (M5000C421)
kpi_info.use: The sum of sampled number of users in Enhanced Cell FACH state. Users having only DL HS_FACH (without HS in uplink) are also counted. UPDATED: Every 100ms the number of users in Enhanced CELL_FACH is sampled and summed to this counter.

kpi_info.title: MAX_EFACH_USERS (M5000C422)
kpi_info.use: The maximum value for concurrent users in Enhanced Cell FACH state. Users having only DL HS_FACH (without HS in uplink) are also counted. UPDATED: The counter is updated over the measurement period. The value of the counter is the maximum value of all samples for the number of users in Enhanced CELL_FACH state.

kpi_info.title: DND_CEDCH_RSRC (M5000C423)
kpi_info.use: The number of PRACH Preambles received by BTS not granted a Common E-DCH Resource. UPDATED: The counter is updated when the PRACH Preamble was not granted and the BTS DSP report for Common E-DCH resource usage contains "Denied E-DCH Resources" indicator.

kpi_info.title: ACTIVE_DC_MIMO_USERS_2C_SUM (M5000C424)
kpi_info.use: The sum of sampled values for the number of active DC-HSDPA MIMO users. Active DC-HSDPA MIMO users use both carriers for transmission. This counter, divided by the denominator M5000C327, provides the average number of active DC-HSDPA MIMO users with two carriers. When this counter is updated the counter M5000C328 is updated as well. UPDATED: The number of DC-HSDPA MIMO users is sampled with 100 ms period and summed to this counter. Only users which use both carriers for transmission within one TTI are counted. The counter is updated for both (primary and secondary) cells.

kpi_info.title: ACTIVE_DC_MIMO_USERS_1C_SUM (M5000C425)
kpi_info.use: The sum of sampled values for the number of active DC-HSDPA MIMO users. Active DC-HSDPA MIMO users use only one carrier for transmission. This counter, divided by the denominator M5000C327, provides the average number of active DC-HSDPA MIMO users with one carrier. When this counter is updated the counter M5000C329 is updated as well. UPDATED: The number of DC-HSDPA MIMO users is sampled with 100 ms period and summed to this counter. Only users which use only one carrier for transmission are counted. The counter is updated only if users receive data in measured cell.

kpi_info.title: CAPABLE_DC_MIMO_USERS_SUM (M5000C426)
kpi_info.use: The sum of sampled values for the number of capable DC-HSDPA MIMO users. When this counter is updated the counter M5000C330 is updated as well. UPDATED: The number of DC-HSDPA MIMO capable users is sampled with 100 ms period and summed to this counter. The counter is updated regardless of the fact whether users receive data or not.

kpi_info.title: HS_DSCH_CRDT_RDCT_BUF_CPU_LOAD (M5000C453)
kpi_info.use: The number of 10ms congestion control iterations in which the Iub throughput of connections originating from CRNC was controlled by Congestion Control. It is based on the trigger "Total shared memory buffer occupancy exceeding maximum allowed value" (FSM release 2 only) or "overload protection of frame protocol processing CPU" (FSM release 2/3 onwards). The counter counts the number of iterations, in which the initial total credit reduction is directly followed. The counter counts the number of iterations, in which the initial total credit reduction is directly followed. And counting continues until the total credits granted to RNC recover and exceed the measured Iub throughput at the time of previous congestion detection by half or until a new throughput reduction is applied with different cause. Note that only one of the M5000C176...C178 or M5000C453 might increment by 2 in 20ms iteration. UPDATED: Congestion Control entity remembers the congestion type of previous total credit reduction. In each 10ms iteration, in case the type was "Total shared memory buffer occupancy exceeding maximum allowed value" (FSM release 2 only) or "Overload protection of frame protocol processing CPU" (FSM release 2/3 onwards) and "Total credits" granted to RNC have not yet recovered from the reduction (with conservative safety margin to account for longer RTTs) it increments M5000C453 by two. This counter no longer increments by the number of queues for which credits were reduced to zero because of connection specific buffer exceeding the maximum value.
